properties.name: Joondanna Community Garden
properties.descriptio: The first of its kind in the City of Stirling! The garden focuses on sustainable living practices including local food production, waste minimisation and management and water conservation.

properties.name: McDougall Farm Community Garden
properties.descriptio: The garden is managed by a group of friendly and passionate volunteers who seek to provide a safe, healthy and enjoyable community enterprise.

properties.name: Urban Orchard
properties.descriptio: Community garden in front of Perth cultural centre.

properties.name: City Farm
properties.descriptio: City Farm, a green oasis surrounded by multi stories building, is ideal for those living in inner-city apartments who may not have access to a garden at home.

properties.name: Fremantle Environmental Resource Network (FERN) Community Garden
properties.descriptio: The community garden is constantly bustling with activity, with a vegan buffet dinner by donation held every Monday and Wednesday nights, as well as gardening busy bees hosted every Tuesday morning.

properties.name: Apace WA
properties.descriptio: At this garden staff and volunteers grow lots of produce market garden style, and community members pay an annual membership fee which entitles them to harvest what they can eat.

properties.name: Earthwise Community Centre
properties.descriptio: The gardens of this old pink church have been transformed by volunteers into sustainable communal gardens featuring quirky recycled sculptures, ponds, compost, an op shop and meeting room.

properties.name: Veggie garden
properties.descriptio: Council has placed herbs garden behind police station.

properties.name: North Perth Community Garden
properties.descriptio: Herbs, vegetables and flowers make up majority of the garden, with a greenhouse, small orchard and native garden present too. Education workshops are also available to the wider community.

properties.name: Pennywort
properties.descriptio: Pennywort near riverbank on the trail to Lesmurdie Falls, but be quick! Somebody will see you.

properties.name: Lai's Kaffle lime leaves
properties.descriptio: Lai grows a big kaffle lime in her house, feel free to pick their leaves or fruits from the tree overhang fence.

properties.name: Wild Funnel
properties.descriptio: South side of Lake Joondalup, access by bike path from Ocean Reef rd.
